laboratory_examinations.findings: Inflammation of the head and uncinate process of the pancreas without evidence for pseudocyst or adjacent vascular compromise. The pancreas is diffusely mildly atrophic. No acute abnormalities in liver, gallbladder, spleen, kidneys, stomach, or colon.
Triglyceride level of 12.6% with reference range 18.0 - 42.0, thus indicating a value below the normal range.
